HEADWORD: mandrill
<hw>man"drill</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧n"dr⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>mandrille</ets>, Sp. <ets>mandril</ets>, It.
<ets>mandrillo</ets>; prob. the native name in Africa. Cf.
<er>Drill</er> an ape.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large West
African baboon (<spn>Papio sphinx</spn> syn. <spn>Mandrillus
sphinx</spn>, formerly <spn>Cynocephalus mormon</spn> syn. <spn>Papio
mormon</spn>). The adult male has, on the sides of the nose, large,
naked, grooved swellings, conspicuously striped with blue and red. It is
an <isa>endangered species</isa>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manduca</ent>⟦br⟧
